What does Bundler mean?

A person or thing who bundle material or products for ease of handling

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- @@
What are bundlers used for?

A bundler is a developement tool that combines many JS code files into a one file that is production ready , loadable in browser

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------@@
Bundler and npm are primarily classified as "Dependency Management" and "Front End Package Manager" tools respectively.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------@@

Is Babel a bundler?

It is a module bundler for JavaScript which compiles small pieces of code into something larger and more complex, such as a library or application

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------@@

What are Bundlers in react JS?

Bundling. Most React apps will have their files “bundled” using tools like Webpack, Rollup or Browserify. Bundling is the process of following imported files 
and merging them into a single file: a “bundle”.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------@@

First of all, what is a JavaScript bundler?

A JavaScript bundler is a tool that puts your code and all its dependencies together in one JavaScript file.
There are many of them out there these days, being the most popular ones browserify and webpack.



